    },
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "# Calling C function with two integers and getting a C string result\nresult = dll.function_in_c_library(5, 10)\nprint(result.decode('utf-8'))"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "_ctypes has been part of the Python standard library since version 2.0 but gained several improvements and additions in Python 3.12+",
    "_Some notable changes in 3.12 include optimized performance, enhanced support for new C types, and simplified memory management"
